@node 5 "Versions..."

V0.9:	not released but seems to work properly.

V1.0:	1st release, 31.3.95 (CAFFEINE)
	- added filetype indicator and the SUPPRESS option.

V2.0:	2nd release, 19.4.95 (SUPREME)
	- added own routine for search in DMSs (MUCH FASTER than DMS VIEWDIZ)
	- optimzed search in executables A LOT!

V2.1:	(no public release)
	- added own routine for search in GIFs (MUCH FASTER than GIFDESC)
	- SnatchDIZ is now reentrant and can be made resident (PURE option)
	- removed KEEPDIZ option because it was unnecessary at all
	- now checks if dos.library is >= V36
	- no longer crunched. V2.0 sometimes crashed on 040 systems due to
	  the used packer (CrunchMania V1.9)

V2.2:	3rd release, 19.7.95 (SHOOT) :-)
	- fixed bug with filenames containing spaces/wildcards
	- I was told SnatchDIZ even handles JPGs, check it out yourself

V2.3:	4th release, 17.8.95
	- added /X style listfile generation
	- fixed small bugs concerning resident ability

V2.4:	5th release, 27.11.95 (HELLFiRE)
	- fixed bug with file_ids longer than 44*15 chars
	- fixed bug with small text-files that could crash the system
	- improved and bugfixed listfile generation (illegal file_ids are
	  now formated as good as possible)

V2.41:	(no public release, 22.1.96)
	- slightly improved listfile generation once again
	- added small dos-script for easier listfile generation
	- optimized code a bit

V2.5:	(no puplic release, 16.6.96)
	- added RAR support

V2.6:	6th release, 25.08.96
	- added diz->filecomment conversion
	- added return codes (why didnt i do that b4?)

V2.7:	7th release, 02.09.96
	- GenListFile dos-script now really included (forgot that in V2.6)
	- improved diz->comment conversion: no more "xxxxxxx" etc.
	- fixed two small bugs (once again the resident fuck)

V2.8:	8th release, 22.06.97
	- added XPK support
	- fixed ZIP extracting (now recognizes uppercase file_ids too)
	  (thanks to Weetabix from IRC for reporting)
	- added hint about wildcard usage in the Usage part of this guide
	  (there is no need for any external program)
@endnode
